text: Cayuga is an unincorporated community in Hinds County, in the U.S. state of Mississippi. ==History== A post office called Cayuga was established in 1829, and remained in operation until 1906. A variant name was "Cayuga Plantation". The community is named after Cayuga Lake, in New York. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Mississippi Category:Unincorporated communities in Hinds County, Mississippi
title: Cayuga, Mississippi
